d delivery of cylinders, drums and vessels is arranged using our dedicated transport fleet with ADR trained drivers or approved ADR trained contractors. Customer deliveries and collections are also accepted.</li>\n</ul>\n',1283196518,1283110118,'',0),('2:c66d88b49010daf95bed7c02deca896e','<h1>Cylinder Testing</h1>\n<p>Legislation in Europe requires that high and low pressure gas cylinders are inspected and tested at regular intervals. It is a legal requirement that this inspection and test can only be carried out by organisations approved under the Transportable Pressure Equipment Directive (TPED).</p>\n<p>gcs is approved to undertake \"In-Service Inspection\" and “pi” marking of transportable pressure receptacles as a Type C Inspection Body, accredited by UKAS to ISO/IEC 17020:1998 within the scope of the TPED.</p>\n<p>The approval covers the following specifications:</p>\n<ul>\n<li> BS EN 1968:2002 + A2:2005 - seamless steel cylinders  </li>\n<li> BS EN 1802:2002 - seamless aluminium cylinders</li>\n<li> BS EN 1803:2002 - welded steel cylinders</li>\n<li> BS EN 1SO 11623 - composite cylinders</li>\n<li> BS EN 14876:2007 - welded steel pressure drums</li>\n<li> EN 14189:2003, procedure A or B - cylinder valves</li>\n<li> GCS Op121 - seamless steel cylinder bundles</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Cylinder processing:</p>\n<ul>\n<li> Facilities are available to inspect, test and refurbish cylinders, drums and vessels including dismantling, cleaning, shot blasting (externally and internally), thread re-machining, collar replacement, painting, re-assembly, oxygen level cleaning, drying to specified levels and dry Nitrogen padding.</li>\n<li> Cylinder test data is electronically recorded on our dedicated shop floor data capture systems.</li>\n<li> Standard sizes accommodated:\n<ul>\n<li> Cylinders up to 100L water capacity; test pressures to 700 bar</li>\n<li> Drums up to 1000L water capacity; test pressures as required</li>\n<li> Vessels up to 2500L water capacity; test pressures to 450 bar</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li> Specials: other sizes may be accommodated by arrangement.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Cylinder ancilliaries</h2>\n<ul>\n<li> Our facilities also cater for the dismantling, refurbishment and reassembly of manifolded cylinder pallets, bundles, frames and cylinder/tube trailers.</li>\n<li> Off site working for decommissioning and re-installation is also provided where required.</li>\n<li> Collection and delivery of cylinders, drums and vessels is arranged using our dedicated transport fleet with ADR trained drivers or approved ADR trained contractors. Customer deliveries and collections are also accepted.</li>\n</ul>\n',1283196550,1283110150,'',0),('2:74d626bf05781e14fbfc63501b7163d7','<p>Where large volumes of high pressure gases are required multiple cylinder units are used. These units can be transported or used as static storage in a variety of configurations, ranging from two to hundreds of cylinders or vessels. </p>\n<p>These units are given a variety of descriptions - MCP\'s (manifolded cylinder pallets), packs, bundles, banks, cascades, storage modules, tubes, tube trailers, cylinder trailers etc</p>\n<p>We provide a number of products and services relating to gas storage equipment including gas control and dispensing systems:</p>\n<ul>\n<li> Design, manufacture and supply.</li>\n<li> Assembly of customer specific equipment</li>\n<li> Installation, commissioning, removal, decommissioning of on site static storage systems</li>\n<li> Refurbishment of existing equipment. (Including the cylinders, which are processed in the same facility in Nottingham).</li>\n</ul>\n',1283196655,1283110255,'',0),('2:c29b2b4a165a012f3ba700e20fb57d0d','<h1> high pressure storage </h1>\n<p>Where large volumes of high pressure gases are required multiple cylinder units are used. These units can be transported or used as static storage in a variety of configurations, ranging from two to hundreds of cylinders or vessels. </p>\n<p>These units are given a variety of descriptions - MCP\'s (manifolded cylinder pallets), packs, bundles, banks, cascades, storage modules, tubes, tube trailers, cylinder trailers etc</p>\n<p>We provide a number of products and services relating to gas storage equipment including gas control and dispensing systems:</p>\n<ul>\n<li> Design, manufacture and supply.</li>\n<li> Assembly of customer specific equipment</li>\n<li> Installation, commissioning, removal, decommissioning of on site static storage systems</li>\n<li> Refurbishment of existing equipment. (Including the cylinders, which are processed in the same facility in Nottingham).</li>\n</ul>\n',1283196682,1283110282,'',0),('2:3642a25e6a97666cd344e37b3b6c0ed0','<h1>RoadGas - CNG/CBM </h1>\n<p>gcs is involved in the use of Natural Gas as a fuel for vehicles. Our range of products consist of:</p>\n<ul>\n<li> Supply of compressed Natural Gas (CNG/CBM) </li>\n<li> Refuelling stations and equipment</li>\n<li> Vehicle fuel cells </li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Supply of CNG - RoadGas  </h2>\n<ul>\n<li> CNG is supplied in a variety of ways to suit our customer needs. Either through our dedicated refueling stations, by tube trailer (complete with dispense systems), mini trailers or transportable bundles.</li>\n<li> Our Natural Gas sources are both fossil and bio-methane. Compressed Bio-methane (CBM) is taken from Liquid Bio-Methane (LBM) and compressed at our station in Nottingham. </li>\n<h2>Refuelling station equipment:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<h2>Refuelling stations</h2>\n<p>We provide a total turnkey package including design, installation and servicing of complete CNG refuelling stations.</p></li>\n<li>\n<h2> Storage</h2>\n<p>We design and build standard or bespoke high pressure CNG storage modules with the option of either single or three line cascades, complete with priority panel and safety valves. We also offer a full retesting and refurbishing service.</p></li>\n<li>\n<h2> Dispensers</h2>\n<p>We supply manual and electronic dispensers and offer service and support.</p></li>\n<li>\n<h2> Fuelmaker©</h2>\n<p>The Fuelmaker© is a small, compact CNG refueling machine ideal for filling vehicles at home or at a depot. It is designed to fill a small van or car, automatically, overnight. gcs are dealers for Fuelmaker© in the UK.</p></li>\n<li>\n<h2>Vehicle CNG fuel cells</h2>\n<p>The onboard CNG vehicle fuel cell consists of high pressure gas cylinders, valves, safety devices, refuelling connection and regulators. These are designed for specific vehicles as bolt on modules. They can be used for on-road and off-road vehicles, forklift trucks and other engine driven equipment. </p></li>\n</ul>\n</ul>',1283197029,1283110629,'',0),('2:c22a907ca8aee721341c6bee5776edd9','<p>gcs employs 65 personnel with long term expertise and skills drawn from the cylinder and gases industries and handles in excess of 500,000 units per year through the Nottingham facility.</p>\n<p>Gas Container Services is committed to reducing environmental impact and use natural gas as a fuel for its large goods vehicles and forklift trucks. </p>\n<div class=\"demo\">\n<div id=\"accordion\">\n<h3><a href=\"#\">Cylinder Testing</a></h3>\n<div>\n<p>                 We  carry out periodic inspection and testing of high and low pressure gas cylinders, vessels and drums. <img class=\"photoleft\" src=\"/sites/all/themes/gcs/images/gcs/cylinderscurlsmall.jpg\" /> Our test shop facilities are fully equipped to fully refurbish cylinders, cylinder pack frames and cylinder trailers to as new condition.  CONTACT???\n                            </p></div>\n<h3><a href=\"#\">Manufacturing</a></h3>\n<div>\n<p>\n                                    We design and manufacture products for the storage, transportation, control and dispense of high pressure gases for a wide range of industrial and breathing applications. CONTACT???\n                                </p>\n</div>\n<h3><a href=\"#\">Roadgas</a></h3>\n<div>\n<p>\n                                  As RoadGas we  design, manufacture, 